events.name: Western Kentucky Hilltoppers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron passed for 219 yards and matched his career high with four touchdown passes to lead No. 1 Alabama to a 35-0 win over Western Kentucky on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: QBs star: Bama's McCarron

events.name: USC Trojans at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Matt Barkley threw a career-best six touchdown passes, and Robert Woods was spectacular with 200 all-purpose yards and two scores, to help No. 2 Southern California shake free of Syracuse 42-29 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barkley throws 6 TDs as No. 2 USC tops Cuse

events.name: Washington Huskies at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Alfred Blue rushed for 101 yards, including a 21-yard score, and No. 3 LSU racked up 242 yards on the ground in a 41-3 victory over Washington on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 Tigers bully Huskies

events.name: Fresno State Bulldogs at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Kenjon Barner ran for 201 yards and three touchdowns to lead No. 4 Oregon to a 42-25 victory over Fresno State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: RB Barner (201 yards, 3 TDs) paces No. 4 Ducks

events.name: Florida A&M Rattlers at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Damien Williams ran for 156 yards and four touchdowns in a record-setting Owen Field debut, Kenny Stills added 120 yards receiving and a score and No. 5 Oklahoma beat Florida A&M 69-13 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sooners' Williams runs for 4 TDs

events.name: Savannah State Tigers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Florida State tops Savannah State 55-0 in shortened game due to weather.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sav. St. down 55 to Fla. St.; game called off

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Aaron Murray hit Marlon Brown for two of his three touchdown passes, the second for the go-ahead score as No. 7 Georgia recover from a shaky start with 32 second-half points that spoiled Missouri's SEC debut in a 41-20 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia recovers to spoil Missouri's SEC debut

events.name: Louisiana Monroe Warhawks at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Kolton Browning's 16-yard touchdown run on fourth-and-one lifted Louisiana-Monroe to a 34-31 overtime win over No. 8 Arkansas.
headlines.shortLinkText: La.-Monroe stuns No. 8 Ark.

events.name: East Carolina Pirates at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Dylan Thompson completed 21 of 37 passes for 330 yards and three touchdowns to help No. 9 South Carolina (2-0) beat East Carolina 48-10 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Carolina improves to 2-0

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Central Michigan Chippewas

headlines.description: Andrew Maxwell threw for 275 yards and two touchdowns, and No. 11 Michigan State cruised to a 41-7 win over Central Michigan on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxwell, Bell pace Michigan St. in blowout

events.name: Ball State Cardinals at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: DeAndre Hopkins caught three touchdown passes, Andre Ellington rushed for two scores and Spencer Benton kicked a 61-yard field goal to set an Atlantic Coast Conference record in No. 12 Clemson's 52-27 victory over Ball State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hopkins, Ellington spark No. 12 Clemson

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Sean Mannion threw for 276 yards and a touchdown, Oregon State's defense smothered Wisconsin's Montee Ball and the Beavers upset the No. 13 Badgers 10-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon State stuns No. 13 Wisconsin

events.name: UCF Knights at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Braxton Miller became the first Ohio State quarterback to rush for three touchdowns in 34 years and he passed for another score to lead the 14th-ranked Buckeyes to a 31-16 victory over Central Florida on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miller runs for 3 TDs, leads OSU

events.name: Austin Peay Governors at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Virginia Tech used two big plays in the punt return game to overcome a lethargic offensive start, and the No. 15 Hokies beat Austin Peay 42-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 15 VT leans on special teams in victory

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Brett Hundley passed for 305 yards and four touchdowns in an outstanding Rose Bowl debut, Datone Jones sacked Taylor Martinez for a tiebreaking safety with 8:44 to play, and UCLA surprised No. 17 Nebraska 36-30 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCLA tops No. 16 Nebraska

events.name: New Mexico Lobos at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Texas quarterback David Ash scored on a 49-yard touchdown run and had receivers turn short throws into two more scores and the No. 17 Longhorns routed New Mexico 45-0 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Longhorns use long TDs to rout New Mexico

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Ka'Deem Carey scored four touchdowns, Matt Scott threw for 320 yards and two scores, and Arizona knocked off No. 18 Oklahoma State 59-38 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 18 Oklahoma St. unravels, upset by Arizona

events.name: Air Force Falcons at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Denard Robinson ran for 218 yards, threw for 208 and scored four times to help No. 19 Michigan hold off Air Force for a 31-25 win Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson's 4 TDs help Michigan by Air Force

events.name: Grambling State Tigers at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: The 20th-ranked Horned Frogs also made Gary Patterson the winningest coach in school history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Patterson becomes TCU's winningest coach

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Collin Klein threw for 210 yards and ran for 71 more Saturday, accounting for four touchdowns and leading No. 21 Kansas State to a 52-13 rout of Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klein leads K-State in rout of Miami

events.name: Purdue Boilermakers at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Tommy Rees came off the bench to lead Notre Dame on a last-minute, winning drive Saturday as the No. 22 Irish got a 27-yard field goal from Kyle Brindza with seven seconds to go and beat Purdue 20-17.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rees rescues Irish in return from ban

events.name: Missouri State Bears at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgewater kept No. 23 Louisville's offense clicking Saturday by passing for a career-high 344 yards and two touchdowns, while the defense stifled Missouri State in a 35-7 rout.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridgewater's career day keeps L'ville hot

events.name: Florida Gators at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Mike Gillislee ran for 83 yards and two touchdowns and No. 24 Florida shut down Texas A&M's offense in the second half in a 20-17 win on Saturday in the Aggies' first Southeastern Conference game after moving from the Big 12.
headlines.shortLinkText: SEC welcome: A&M loses

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Drew Terrell returned a punt 75 yards for a score and caught a 19-yard touchdown pass, Ed Reynolds took one of his two interceptions for another touchdown and No. 25 Stanford rebounded from a disappointing debut to roll past Duke 50-13 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Terrell, Reynolds help Stanford steamroll Duke

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Mike Glennon threw a 46-yard third-quarter touchdown to receiver Bryan Underwood and North Carolina State held on to beat Connecticut 10-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC State hangs on to beat UConn in tight game

events.name: New Hampshire Wildcats at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: MarQueis Gray threw for two touchdowns and ran for two more by halftime, and Minnesota finally enjoyed an easy victory over an FCS-level opponent by beating New Hampshire 44-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gray's 4-TD first half leads Minnesota in romp

events.name: Tulane Green Wave at Tulsa Golden Hurricane

headlines.description: Alex Singleton ran for 106 yards and three touchdowns to lead Tulsa to a 45-10 victory over Tulane on Saturday in a game marred by a serious injury to Tulane safety Devon Walker.
headlines.shortLinkText: Safety Walker injured in Tulane's loss to Tulsa

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Temple Owls

headlines.description: Perry Hills threw two touchdowns and ran for one to help Maryland beat Temple 36-27 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland builds big lead, holds off Temple

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Michael Rocco hit Jake McGee on a 6-yard touchdown pass with 1:28 to play Saturday, and Sam Ficken's fourth missed field goal of the game -- from 42 yards at the gun -- preserved the Cavaliers' 17-16 victory over Penn State.
headlines.shortLinkText: 4 missed FGs doom Penn St. at UVa

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Tyler Russell threw for 222 yards and three touchdowns, Marcus Green caught two touchdown passes and Mississippi State easily beat Auburn 28-10 on Saturday at Davis Wade Stadium.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell tosses 3 TDs, lifts Miss. St. past Auburn

events.name: Maine Black Bears at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Chase Rettig threw three touchdown passes as Boston College routed Maine.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rettig (3 TD passes) leads BC to rout of Maine

events.name: Southern Utah Thunderbirds at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: California cornerback Marc Anthony scored on a 61-yard interception return in the fourth quarter and the Golden Bears shook off another sluggish start at home to beat Southern Utah 50-31 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cal overcomes sluggish start, defeats S. Utah

events.name: Sacramento State Hornets at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Edgar Castaneda's 30-yard field goal as time expired gave Sacramento State a stunning 30-28 win over Colorado on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: FCS Sac. St. tops Colo. with FG as time expires

headlines.shortLinkText: BYU 45, Weber St. 13

events.name: Eastern Washington Eagles at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Jeff Tuel threw a pair of touchdown passes to Isiah Myers as Washington State hung on to beat Eastern Washington 24-20 on Saturday in the home debut of Cougars coach Mike Leach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leach picks up first win with Washington State

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at UMass Minutemen

headlines.description: Tre Roberson scored on runs of 50 and 39 yards before leaving with an apparent left leg injury, and Indiana spoiled Massachusetts' first home game as a Football Bowl Subdivision member with a 45-6 win on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana loses QB Roberson, romps over UMass

events.name: Howard Bison at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Gary Nova threw two touchdown passes to Brandon Coleman and Rutgers' swarming defense limited Howard to 149 total yards Saturday, giving Kyle Flood a 26-0 victory in his first home game as the Scarlet Knights' coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutgers' D delivers Flood's first home victory

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Steele Jantz threw for 241 yards and the game's only touchdown on Saturday and Iowa State beat Iowa 9-6 for its first win in Iowa City in 10 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa State's win in Iowa City its first in 10 years

events.name: Rice Owls at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Chris Boswell's fourth field goal, a 45-yarder as time expired, lifted Rice to a come-from-behind 25-24 victory Saturday over Kansas.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boswell's four field goals lift Rice past Kansas

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Nevada Wolf Pack

headlines.description: B.J. Daniels passed for 363 yards and three touchdowns, including a 56-yard scoring toss to Andre Davis with 38 seconds left in the game Saturday, to help South Florida come from behind to beat Nevada 32-31.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Florida ekes by Nevada with last-minute TD

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Tanner Price scored on a 1-yard sneak with 2:09 left to help Wake Forest rally past North Carolina 28-27 on Saturday in the Atlantic Coast Conference opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Price's late QB sneak pushes Wake past UNC

events.name: Georgia State Panthers at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Justin Hunter tied a school single-game record Saturday by catching three of Tyler Bray's four touchdown passes, as Tennessee trounced Football Championship Subdivision program Georgia State 51-13 in its home opener Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hunter catches three TDs in Tennessee's rout
